<div class=3D"step_num" aria-hidden=3D"true">2</div><div class=3D"step">
<b class=3D"whb" aria-hidden=3D"true">Know the LARS mnemonic.</b> For movin=
g decimal places, =E2=80=9CLARS=E2=80=9D is a handy memory device. It stand=
s for =E2=80=9CLeft-Add, Right-Subtract.=E2=80=9D This tells you what to do=
 with the decimal point if you wish to either add or subtract to change exp=
onents. If you want to convert your measurement from a small exponent to a =
larger one, you will be adding units to the exponent, and for each one addi=
tion to the exponent, you will move the decimal point one space to the left=
. Moving from a larger unit of measure to a smaller, you will be subtractin=
g exponents, which will involve moving the decimal point to the right.
<ul><li>For example, consider converting kilometers to meters. A kilometer =
is <span class=3D"mwe-math-element"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline m=
we-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;" data-original-text=3D"10^{3}"=
><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaysty=
le 10^{3}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mn>10</mn>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>3</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 10^{3}}</anno=
tation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/9dbd60b35ef8ca5859f59d14662a63139ffe0a50" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical-align: -0.338ex; widt=
h:3.379ex; height:2.676ex;" alt=3D"10^{3}"></span> meters, but the single m=
eter is <span class=3D"mwe-math-element"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inl=
ine mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;" data-original-text=3D"10=
^{0}"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displ=
aystyle 10^{0}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mn>10</mn>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 10^{0}}</anno=
tation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/45d6ef004bb97df6bf6ee2ec20f8eec7aa32adcb" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical-align: -0.338ex; widt=
h:3.379ex; height:2.676ex;" alt=3D"10^{0}"></span>. Thus, you want to subtr=
act 3 in the exponent, so you will move the decimal to the right three plac=
es ("Left-Add, RIGHT-SUBTRACT"). Therefore, if you begin with a measure of =
1.234 km, you would make the following change to meters:
<ul>
<li>1.234 km ............(original unit)</li>
<li>12.34 .................(move decimal one space right)</li>
<li>123.4..................(move decimal two spaces right)</li>
<li>1,234 m..................(move decimal three spaces right)</li>
</ul>
</li></ul>
</div>
