<b class=3D"whb" aria-hidden=3D"true">Move the decimal as needed.</b> For t=
his example, suppose you have the measurement of a germ at 2,600 nm. You ne=
ed to move the decimal point 9 spaces to the left. Since this is a whole nu=
mber with no decimal point showing, you can insert the decimal at the end o=
f the number and then count the spaces to move it. When you run out of numb=
ers, you will fill in all remaining spaces with zeroes.<sup id=3D"_ref-7" c=
lass=3D"reference" aria-label=3D"Link to Reference 7"><a href=3D"https://ww=
