<div class=3D"tips_li_div">To help remember some of the most common units o=
f measure in the metric system, recall the sentence, =E2=80=9CKing Hector D=
ied Monday Drinking Chocolate Milk.=E2=80=9D The initials of these words, K=
-H-D-M-D-C-M, represent the common prefixes in the metric system, in decrea=
sing decimal positions: Kilo- (10<sup>3</sup>), Hecto- (10<sup>2</sup>), De=
ka- (10<sup>1</sup>), Meter/Gram/Liter (10<sup>0</sup>), Deci- (10<sup>-1</=
sup>), Centi- (10<sup>-2</sup>), Milli (10<sup>-3</sup>). The nanometer dis=
cussed in this article is at 10<sup>-9</sup>, which is too far down the sca=
le for this memory device.<div class=3D"clearall tips_li_div"></div>
</div>
